sentences: Lori Balmer (born 1960) is an Australian pop singer, recording artist and worked as a session singer and model; and has appeared on TV in Australia, United States, Japan, Europe and Britain.
Lori Balmer was born in 1960, and started singing professionally at an early age.
Her debut single, "Banjo Boy", was issued early in 1966, under the name Lori, via RCA Records and includes an orchestra directed by Tommy Tycho.
These were issued as her fourth single, in 1967.
In January 1968, following an invitation from Barry Gibb, Balmer travelled to England with her parents and they initially stayed with the Gibb family.
In July 1968 she recorded two songs written by the Gibb brothers, "Treacle Brown" and "Four Faces West".
Balmer released it as a single via Polydor Records, in November 1968.
In 1971 Balmer signed to Pye Records, with Tony Atkins producing her single, "Here Before the Sun", which appeared in 1972.

In 1971 Balmer signed to Pye Records, with Tony Atkins producing her single, "Here Before the Sun", which appeared in 1972.
In the mid- to late 1970s, she released singles in Australia, under the name Lori Balmer, where she also toured as a backing singer for Cold Chisel and for Richard Clapton.
She sang the title song of the Australian movie, Melvin, Son of Alvin (1984).
In 1987 she provided backing vocals on the soundtracks of the Australian film, Sons of Steel and, in 1995, Billy's Holiday.
In 1987 she provided backing vocals on the soundtracks of the Australian film, Sons of Steel and, in 1995, Billy's Holiday.
Through the 1990s to the present Balmer has worked as one of Australia's top session singers and owns a successful marketing company.
